              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G6/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G6/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G6/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Streams in the topos of trees">Streams in the topos of trees</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Presheaves on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\omega ]]></fr:tex> — the
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/birkedalFirstStepsSGDT2012/" title="First steps in synthetic guarded domain theory: step-indexing in the topos of trees" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/birkedalFirstStepsSGDT2012/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/birkedalFirstStepsSGDT2012/" type="local">topos of trees</fr:link> — are the usual setting
for this kind of guarded reasoning: step-indexing, later, and Löb in
their classical form.</html:p>
            <html:p>There one solves <html:em>guarded domain equations</html:em>. Streams over a set
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> satisfy
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Str} \;\cong \; A \times  \rhd  \mathrm {Str},]]></fr:tex>
and since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \mapsto  A \times  \rhd  X]]></fr:tex> is
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link>, the equation has a
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00GE/" title="Fixed points of locally contractive functors are unique" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00GE/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00GE/" type="local">unique solution</fr:link>, and
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" title="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" type="local">every coalgebra unfolds uniquely</fr:link>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/" type="external">https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G3/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G3/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G3/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Towers of Hanoi by Löb induction">Towers of Hanoi by Löb induction</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Move <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> disks from one peg to another using a third. The functor
of subproblems is
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[H X\,{\mathopen {}\left (0\right )\mathclose {}} = \top ,
   \qquad 
   H X\,{\mathopen {}\left (n+1\right )\mathclose {}} = X{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}} \times  X{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link> because its argument appears only at
the strictly smaller stage.</html:p>
            <html:p>The coalgebra decomposes a problem — pegs labelled source, target,
spare — at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex> into the two rotated subproblems: the tower moves
to the spare peg, then onto the relocated largest disk. The algebra
joins a pair of move lists around the move of that disk:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (l, r\right )\mathclose {}} \;\mapsto \;
   l \mathbin {++} {\mathopen {}\left  [\mathrm {move}\right  ]\mathclose {}} \mathbin {++} r.]]></fr:tex></html:p>
            <html:p>The <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" title="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" type="local">hylomorphism</fr:link> of this coalgebra and algebra is the
solution; its unfolding is the recurrence
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathrm {hanoi}\,{\mathopen {}\left (n+1\right )\mathclose {}} =
   \mathrm {hanoi}\,{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}} \mathbin {++}
   {\mathopen {}\left  [\mathrm {move}\right  ]\mathclose {}} \mathbin {++}
   \mathrm {hanoi}\,{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
and taking lengths gives the move count <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2^n - 1]]></fr:tex> by induction.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/" type="external">https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G2/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G2/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G2/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Karatsuba multiplication by Löb induction">Karatsuba multiplication by Löb induction</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Multiply <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> using three half-size multiplications
instead of four. Split both numbers at a half-width base <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[x = x_0 + B \cdot  x_1,
   \qquad 
   y = y_0 + B \cdot  y_1.]]></fr:tex>
Over pairs of numbers measured by a bound on their digit count, the
functor of subproblems requests the three products
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[X{\mathopen {}\left (x_0, y_0\right )\mathclose {}},
   \qquad 
   X{\mathopen {}\left (x_1, y_1\right )\mathclose {}},
   \qquad 
   X{\mathopen {}\left (x_1 + x_0,\; y_1 + y_0\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
each at a strictly smaller digit bound —
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link> by that certificate.</html:p>
            <html:p>The coalgebra performs the split. The motive at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (x, y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sum _{p} {\mathopen {}\left (p = x \cdot  y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> — a number with a proof that it is
the product — so the recursive results arrive as
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[z_0 = x_0 y_0,
   \qquad 
   z_2 = x_1 y_1,
   \qquad 
   z_{11} = {\mathopen {}\left (x_1 + x_0\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (y_1 + y_0\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
each with its proof, and the algebra recombines them through
Karatsuba's identity
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[x \cdot  y
   = z_2 \cdot  B^2 + {\mathopen {}\left (z_{11} - z_2 - z_0\right )\mathclose {}} \cdot  B + z_0,]]></fr:tex>
its one proof obligation.</html:p>
            <html:p>The <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" title="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" type="local">hylomorphism</fr:link> of this coalgebra and algebra is the
multiplier: it evaluates on numerals, correct by the type of its
result.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/" type="external">https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G1/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G1/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G1/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Binary search by Löb induction">Binary search by Löb induction</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Decide whether a query <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex> occurs in a sorted list. Over lists
measured by length, the functor of subproblems either answers
outright or hands over a strictly shorter list with a membership
equivalence:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[H X\,{\mathopen {}\left (\mathit {xs}\right )\mathclose {}} =
   {\mathopen {}\left (q \in  \mathit {xs}\right )\mathclose {}}
   \;+\; {\mathopen {}\left (q \notin  \mathit {xs}\right )\mathclose {}}
   \;+\; \sum _{\mathit {ys} \prec  \mathit {xs}}
   {\mathopen {}\left (q \in  \mathit {xs} \iff  q \in  \mathit {ys}\right )\mathclose {}}
   \times  X{\mathopen {}\left (\mathit {ys}\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link> by the length certificate.</html:p>
            <html:p>The coalgebra splits at the midpoint and compares:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {aligned}
   q = \mathit {mid} &\;:\;\; q \in  \mathit {xs} \text { — done;}\\
   q < \mathit {mid} &\;:\;\; q \in  \mathit {xs}
     \iff  q \in  \mathit {lo};\\
   q > \mathit {mid} &\;:\;\; q \in  \mathit {xs}
     \iff  q \in  \mathit {hi};
   \end {aligned}]]></fr:tex></html:p>
            <html:p>The <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" title="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" type="local">hylomorphism</fr:link> of this coalgebra and algebra is
binary search: on a concrete list it evaluates to a membership
witness with its index, or to a refutation.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/" type="external">https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FZ/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FZ/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FZ/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Euclid's algorithm by Löb induction">Euclid's algorithm by Löb induction</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Compute the greatest common divisor of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, following
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectAlgorithms2025-preprint/" title="Intrinsically Correct Algorithms and Recursive Coalgebras" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectAlgorithms2025-preprint/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/alexandruIntrinsicallyCorrectAlgorithms2025-preprint/" type="local">Alexandru, Urbat, and Wißmann</fr:link>.
Over pairs measured by their second component, the functor of
subproblems is
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[H X\,{\mathopen {}\left (m, 0\right )\mathclose {}} = \top ,
   \qquad 
   H X\,{\mathopen {}\left (m, n\right )\mathclose {}} = X{\mathopen {}\left (n,\, m \bmod  n\right )\mathclose {}}
   \quad  {\mathopen {}\left (n > 0\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link> because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m \bmod  n < n]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>The coalgebra tests <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>. The algebra carries the correctness: at
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m, 0\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> it yields <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> with a proof that it is a greatest
common divisor, and at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m, n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> it transports a gcd of
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (n, m \bmod  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to one of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m, n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>The <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" title="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" type="local">hylomorphism</fr:link> of this coalgebra and algebra is
Euclid's algorithm together with its correctness; its unfolding is
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\gcd {\mathopen {}\left (m, 0\right )\mathclose {}} = m,
   \qquad 
   \gcd {\mathopen {}\left (m, n\right )\mathclose {}} = \gcd {\mathopen {}\left (n,\, m \bmod  n\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd {\mathopen {}\left (12, 8\right )\mathclose {}} = 4]]></fr:tex> by evaluation.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/" type="external">https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive">Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is a
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link> endofunctor on presheaves over a
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" title="Direct categories" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" type="local">direct category</fr:link>, then every value of the
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FV/" title="The coalgebra-to-algebra profunctor" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FV/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FV/" type="local">profunctor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Hylo}]]></fr:tex> is a singleton: every coalgebra is
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" title="Recursive coalgebras and corecursive algebras" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" type="local">recursive</fr:link> and every algebra is corecursive.</html:p>
            <html:p>The proof is one application of <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" title="Löb induction for presheaves on a direct category" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" type="local">Löb</fr:link>. A hylomorphism from
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> is a fixed point of
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[h \mapsto  c \star  F h \star  \alpha ]]></fr:tex>
on the presheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \Rightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> of morphisms. Local contractivity
factors this assignment through <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rhd {\mathopen {}\left (X \Rightarrow  B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, so Löb
provides a fixed point and provides it uniquely.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
