            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Later on presheaves">Later on presheaves</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>The <html:em>later</html:em> modality on presheaves is given at each object by
mapping out of the <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FL/" title="The strict downset sieve of a direct category" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FL/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FL/" type="local">strict downset</fr:link>:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\rhd  P\right )\mathclose {}}\,{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}} = \mathsf {Psh}\,\mathcal {C}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {StrictDown}{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}},\, P\right )\mathclose {}}.]]></fr:tex>
An element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rhd  P]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is a coherent choice of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>-elements
for all objects strictly smaller than <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Restriction in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rhd  P]]></fr:tex> along <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : y \to  x]]></fr:tex> precomposes with the
induced map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {StrictDown}{\mathopen {}\left (y\right )\mathclose {}} \to  \mathsf {StrictDown}{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. At an object of minimal degree the
strict downset is empty, so <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rhd  P]]></fr:tex> is trivial there.</html:p>
            <html:p>Via functoriality, every presheaf restricts to smaller indices: the map
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathsf {next} : P \to  \rhd  P]]></fr:tex>
sends an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> to the family of all its restrictions
along morphisms from strictly lower objects.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
